  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The overall tensile strength range of the investigated steel is ~855±35 MPa with total elongation 65±5% (room temperature).",
    "RD sample higher strain hardening ability attributed to more martensite formation due to higher strain in austenite under iso-strain condition.",
    "OC model (α=1.35, β=2, n=2) successfully describes martensite fraction evolution; RD data matched by considering 1.15× higher plastic strain in austenite compared to TD.",
    "Texture of δ-ferrite is {100}<011> rotated cube with max intensity 2.57; its effect on anisotropic hardening considered insignificant.",
    "Taylor factor: 2.83 (RD) and 2.78 (TD).",
    "Lattice strain measurements show austenite yields first (deviation from linearity at 1.8% strain RD, 2.1% TD) while ferrite yields later (2.3% RD, 2.9% TD).",
    "Strain-induced α'-martensite fraction negligible below 0.03 true strain; at high strains difference between RD and TD martensite fraction up to 4 vol.%.",
    "In RD sample, δ-ferrite and γ+α aggregates deform in iso-strain condition; in TD sample, iso-stress condition leads to strain concentration in δ-ferrite."
  ]
}